title: Full entry list for Monster Energy Cup Series at Atlanta Motor Speedway
text:
"Rocket Man" has two top fives and nine top-10 finishes in 24 races. Â© Russell LaBounty/LAT Photo USA Russell LaBounty 22 Matt DiBenedetto 
DiBenedetto finished ninth in the Daytona 500 and he's hoping to back it up with a respectable result this weekend. Jasen Vinlove Jasen Vinlove-USA TODAY Sports 23 Jeffrey Earnhardt 
Earnhardt will be back in the No. 33 for Cicle Sport/TMG Chevrolet with crew cheif Pat Tryson. , LAT Images www.latphoto.co.uk Russell LaBounty 24 
Cassill had a disasterous race at the 1.5-mile oval in 2016, finishing 36th. 25 
Buescher wants to improve on his 28th-place result at Atlanta last season. , LAT Images www.latimages.co.uk Nigel Kinrade 26 
Ragan's best finish at Atlanta is eighth in 2008. , LAT Images www.latphoto.co.uk Russell LaBounty 27 Kurt Busch 
The newest Daytona 500 champion is stout at Atlanta with three wins, six top fives and 11 top-10 finishes. He also started on pole for this race in 2016. 28 Kyle Larson 
Atlanta is known for its multipe-groove racing, so look for Larson to take the high line to the front on Sunday. , LAT Images www.latimages.co.uk Nigel Kinrade 29 
Unlike last year, Almirola is hoping not to burn his bacon at Atlanta. Getty Images Kevin C. Cox 30 
In 11 races at Atlanta, Allmendinger has three top-10 finishes. , LAT Images www.latphoto.co.uk Russell LaBounty 31 
The seven-time Cup champion is the defending winner of the Folds of Honro QuikTrip 500. Getty Images Getty Images 32 Cody Ware 
Ware drove a number of XFINITY Series race in 2016 and now he's moving up to Cup. He's scheduled to drive the No. 51 Chevrolet. 33 Derrick Cope 
The 1992 Daytona 500 champion will pilot the No. 55 Premium Motorsports Chevrolet driven by Sorenson last Sunday. , LAT Images www.latphoto.co.uk John K Harrelson 34 Cole Whitt 
Whitt will be in the No. 72 TriStar Motorsports Ford Fusion with crew chief Frankie Kerr. Jasen Vinlove Jasen Vinlove-USA TODAY Sports 35 Erik Jones 
In his second startin the new No. 77 Furniture Row Racing Toyota, Jones will compete in his first Monster Energy Cup Series race at Atlanta. , LAT Images www.latphoto.co.uk John K Harrelson 36 Martin Truex Jr. 
In the last three seasons, Truex has driven the No. 78 Furniture Row Racing Toyota to finishes of 23rd, sixth and seventh at Atlanta, respectively. , LAT Images www.latphoto.co.uk Nigel Kinrade 37 Corey LaJoie 
After crashing early in the Daytona 500, LeJoie will be back in the No. 83 BK Racing Toyota. AP 38 Dale Earnhardt Jr. 
After a crash spoiled his Cup return at Daytona, Earnhardt looks to rebound. He has one win, 10 top fives and 14 top-10 finishes at Atlanta. , LAT Images www.latphoto.co.uk Nigel Kinrade 39 Michael McDowell 
McDowell's best Atlanta finish came in 2014 where he finished 27th in the No. 95 Leavine Family Racing Chevy. , LAT Images www.latphoto.co.uk Russell LaBounty
